West Africa Rice Production to Rise Next Year, USDA Unit Says

-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 
2011-05-11T19:26:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/west-africa-rice-production-to-rise-next-year-usda-unit-says.html
Milled-rice production from 12
countries in West Africa may rise to 4.462 million metric tons
in the year that begins Oct. 1 from an estimated 4.063 million
tons in the previous 12 months, according to a unit of the U.S.
Department of Agriculture.  Production in  Mali , the biggest producer, will jump to 1.7
million tons from 1.523 million, the USDAâ€™s Foreign Agriculture
Service said in a  report  posted today on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
